reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits my Oster counter top oven.
reviews.reviewText: Got these as replacements for my Oster counter top oven tray. It's getting grungy. They fit so perfect that they even slide into the track meant for the tray! Good quality aluminum. Not flimsy, very sturdy. Nicely rolled edge & no sharp edges or corners.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2022
reviews.reviewText: These small baking sheets were exactly what I was looking for. Regular-sized cookie sheets or biscuit pans were too big for the small number of biscuits I make for my husband and me. I wanted something small enough to hold just 4-6 biscuits and these were perfect. Being made of stainless steel makes clean-up easy and they are maintaining their color and finish. So far I have used them multiple times and the max baking temperature I have used them at is 425° with no warping noticed. These pans are quite sturdy and maintain their shape quite well. I do not forsee any problems with their ability to keep their shape. I am using them in a regular oven and am really pleased with this purchase. If I ever need more I will certainly purchase this product again. I may buy some more just to ahve them on hand!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great pans. Very easy to clean. But they will pop out of shape at temperatures as low as 400 degrees. You’ll hear a loud popping noise and you’ll see the pan is slightly bent in a diagonal line. But do not worry. After you take the pan out and let it cool, it’ll pop back into its original shape and be good as new.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quality, very pleased
reviews.reviewText: I don't cook large batches, and these smaller trays fit perfectly in my countertop oven. They're Very sturdy, which allows me to roast meats and poultry without having to worry about a pan that might buckle under the weight when being moved. I'll be getting a Lot of excellent use out of these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nice quality, easy to clean. Slight buckle in oven even if oven is set to 325°. Haven't washed in dish washer yet just hand washed. Will review again after several months of use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars meaurement is base of pan, edge of lip is a touch larger
reviews.reviewText: the 12" pan was just the tiniest bit too big to fit onto my 13" wide kitchen-aide toaster oven shelf. I mean, it can slide in, but it touches the edges, so no air would be able to circulate. Measurement seems to be of the bottom of the pan, which is 12", top edge of lip flares out just a little bit putting it closer to 12.5" which was a bit too snug for what I wanted.OTOH, these pans are the perfect size to proof 6 bagels in the fridge overnight and fit on my fridge shelves much better than trying to get a full sized pan maneuvered in there. I can't say how they react to heat as I bake my bagels on a pizza stone, but I've been hand washing and rack drying them weekly for a bit now and no signs of rust. Beautiful shine. Nice solid, heavy pan. No warping or flexing when cold.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars still look great
reviews.reviewText: As I was looking for a smaller size pan, I made sure to use this same company. These baking sheets are durable, haven't warped, and I put them right in the dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Like the stainless steel
reviews.reviewText: I like the stainless steel look. But they are too small for big batches of cookies 🍪 I used them for drip pans for baking pies.

Although these trays sometimes bend with the oven heat it is only when there is not a lot on them, and they always reform. They are very easy to clean and cook beautifully, and I am glad to be finally rid of my old, unhealthy 'non-stick' trays
